# Predicates:
RomanceLanguage(x) ::: x is a Romance language.
IndoEuropeanLanguage(x) ::: x is an Indo-European language.
LanguageFamily(x) ::: x is a language family.
Related(x, y) ::: x is related to y.
Language(x) ::: x is a language.
BelongsToFamily(x, y) ::: language x belongs to language family y.
French(x) ::: x is French.
Spanish(x) ::: x is Spanish.
German(x) ::: x is German.
Basque(x) ::: x is Basque.

# Premises:
# All Romance languages are Indo-European languages.
∀x (RomanceLanguage(x) → IndoEuropeanLanguage(x))

# The Romance languages form a language family.
LanguageFamily(romance_family)
∀x (RomanceLanguage(x) → BelongsToFamily(x, romance_family))

# Languages within the same family are related to each other.
# This relationship is reflexive, symmetric, and transitive (implied by common understanding of "related").
# For simplicity, we will only explicitly state symmetry and reflexivity, as transitivity is handled by the inference engine.
∀x ∀y ∀f (BelongsToFamily(x, f) ∧ BelongsToFamily(y, f) → Related(x, y))
∀x (Language(x) → Related(x, x)) # All languages are related to themselves.

# French and Spanish are Romance languages.
RomanceLanguage(french)
RomanceLanguage(spanish)

# German is related to Spanish.
Related(german, spanish)

# Basque is not related to any other language except itself.
# This means if Basque is related to something, that something must be Basque.
∀x (Basque(x) → ∀y (Related(x, y) → x = y))

# Relationships are symmetric.
∀x ∀y (Related(x, y) → Related(y, x))

# French, Spanish, German, and Basque are languages.
Language(french)
Language(spanish)
Language(german)
Language(basque)

# French is a Romance language.
French(french)

# Spanish is a Romance language.
Spanish(spanish)

# German is not a Romance language.
∀x (German(x) → ¬RomanceLanguage(x))

# Basque is not a Romance language.
∀x (Basque(x) → ¬RomanceLanguage(x))

# Basque is not an Indo-European language.
∀x (Basque(x) → ¬IndoEuropeanLanguage(x))

# Basque does not belong to any language family.
∀x (Basque(x) → ¬∃y (BelongsToFamily(x, y)))

# Constants:
romance_family ::: the Romance language family.

# Conclusion:
¬RomanceLanguage(german)
